      "message": "I\u0027m not entirely sure this is right. Currently `cue mod resolve` is documented like this:\n\n\u003e It only consults local information - it works lexically\n\u003e with respect to the registry configuration (see \"cue help registryconfig\")\n\u003e and does not make any network calls to check whether\n\u003e the module exists.\n\nbut ISTM that this is somewhat breaking that contract (it might not be making network calls, but it\u0027s certainly not acting purely lexically).\n\nI wonder if it might be better to have an explicit method that can be invoked to check things can init OK.",
